Canadians are growing increasingly anxious about the state of the economy but are much less concerned about terrorism than they were just months ago, a new poll suggests.

According to numbers released by the Angus Reid Institute on Tuesday, nearly half of Canadians (47 per cent) say the economy is the biggest national concern. That's a jump of 10 percentage points from December.

Prime Minister Justin Trudeau goes face-to-face with Finance Minister Bill Morneau at Rideau Hall in Ottawa on Wednesday, November 4,
